'''Good law''' is the concept in [[case law|jurisprudence]] that a legal decision is still valid. That is, that a decision has not been overturned (during an [[appeal]]) or otherwise rendered obsolete (such as by a change in the underlying law).<ref>{{cite web|title="Cite Checking"|url=http://nationalparalegal.edu/public_documents/courseware_asp_files/researchLitigation/LegalResearch/CiteChecking.asp|website=National Paralegal College|accessdate=21 August 2016}}</ref>

